        itineraire: "Your driver leaves Nantes via the eastern ring road and takes the N23 along the north bank of the Loire. This road passes through Mauves-sur-Loire (a pretty wine village), Le Cellier (whose Château de Clermont offers panoramic Loire views) and Oudon (with its medieval tower visible from afar). The landscape alternates between Coteaux d'Ancenis vineyards, Loire meadows and river views. Arrival in Ancenis is via the suspension bridge that majestically spans the Loire. The A11 alternative (Paris — Nantes motorway) is 5 minutes faster but involves a €3.50 toll. Your driver chooses the optimal route based on traffic. Allow 35 minutes via the N23, 30 minutes via the A11.",
